notes:
&shy;




			CIM22EAPP1-01-08 is an intermediate-maturing, high-yielding, white maize hybrid with drought tolerance, nitrogen-use efficiency, and resistance to GLS, TLB, ear rots, MLN, and rust. It is notable for exceptional yield potential under optimum management and MLN disease pressure, and excellent seed producibility characteristics.

			General... | Abiotic Stress Tolerance: Drought tolerant, Nitrogen-use efficient (NUE) | Adaptation: Mid-altitudes | Biotic Stress Tolerance: Ear rots, Grey leaf spot (GLS), Maize Lethal Necrosis (MLN), Maize streak virus (MSV), Rust, Turcicum leaf blight (TLB) | Grain Color: White grain | Grain Texture: Semi-flint | Maturity Group: Intermediate maturing | Seed producibility traits: Good nicking

&shy;




			Quality Protein Maize (QPM) is an affordable option for alleviating protein malnutrition and reducing animal feed costs. QPM looks and tastes the same as normal maize but contains higher levels of the essential amino acids lysine and tryptophan. Eating QPM is especially beneficial for children who survive on a maize-dominated diet. 

			General... | Adaptation: Highlands, Lowlands, Mid-altitudes | Biofortification: Quality Protein | Biotic Stress Tolerance: Grey leaf spot (GLS), Maize streak virus (MSV), Rust, Turcicum leaf blight (TLB) | Grain Color: White grain | Grain Texture: Semi-flint | Maturity Group: Intermediate maturing | Seed producibility traits: Good nicking

